quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  9,115,"And Allāh would not let a people stray after He has guided them until He makes clear to them what they should avoid. Indeed, Allāh is Knowing of all things."
  9,116,"Indeed, to Allāh belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth; He gives life and causes death. And you have not besides Allāh any protector or any helper."
  9,117,"Allāh has already forgiven the Prophet and the Muhājireen and the Anṣār who followed him in the hour of difficulty after the hearts of a party of them had almost inclined [to doubt], and then He forgave them. Indeed, He was to them Kind and Merciful."
  10,73,"And they denied him, so We saved him and those with him in the ship and made them successors, and We drowned those who denied Our signs. Then see how was the end of those who were warned."
  10,74,"Then We sent after him messengers to their peoples, and they came to them with clear proofs. But they were not to believe in that which they had denied before.{1} Thus We seal over the hearts of the transgressors.",footnotes:1:[i.e., the succeeding generations were persistent in disbelief.]
  10,75,"Then We sent after them Moses and Aaron to Pharaoh and his establishment with Our signs, but they behaved arrogantly and were a criminal people."
  11,40,"[So it was], until when Our command came and the oven overflowed,{1} We said, ",footnotes:1:[As a sign to Noah of the imminence of the flood.  The tannūr is a large, rounded oven.  The word can also mean the earth's lowlands.]
  11,41,"And [Noah] said, "
  11,42,"And it sailed with them through waves like mountains, and Noah called to his son who was apart [from them], "
  12,1,"Alif, Lām, Rā.{1} These are the verses of the clear Book.",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 2:1.]
  12,2,"Indeed, We have sent it down as an Arabic Qur’ān{1} that you might understand.",footnotes:1:[i.e., revealed in the Arabic language.]
  12,3,"We relate to you, [O Muḥammad], the best of stories in what We have revealed to you of this Qur’ān although you were, before it, among the unaware."